{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847090209,"sessionID":"ses_28743f8f0ffeMF8CEy3M1Ky4Ux","part":{"id":"prt_d78bc2345001h2fUCy8qNFDgKa","messageID":"msg_d78bc16ba001PgT1NN0OXBnv51","sessionID":"ses_28743f8f0ffeMF8CEy3M1Ky4Ux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3623ee4112e54aeb95ecaf4b56f63efa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: [To be filled]\n\n(End of file - total 3 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Implementation Summary\n\n[To be filled]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775847090132,"end":1775847090208}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847090241,"sessionID":"ses_28743f8f0ffeMF8CEy3M1Ky4Ux","part":{"id":"prt_d78bc27b7001rGZSCV6tqo8sVR","messageID":"msg_d78bc16ba001PgT1NN0OXBnv51","sessionID":"ses_28743f8f0ffeMF8CEy3M1Ky4Ux","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-18aee9c61703405db0a5474b96e1a23b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 Design — K8s Reconciler Controller\n2: \n3: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language**: Go  \n5: **Size**: L  \n6: **Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime, providing automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: This AR implements a proper Kubernetes reconciler pattern using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. The reconcilers will watch for changes to these CRDs and automatically manage the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources, updating status conditions and ensuring the desired state is achieved.\n11: \n12: ### Key Requirements\n13: \n14: - Watch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs for create/update/delete events\n15: - Reconcile sandbox resources using the agent-sandbox API\n16: - Maintain accurate status conditions (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n17: - Handle spec changes gracefully (rolling updates, reconfiguration)\n18: - Implement proper event recording and finalizer handling\n19: - Provide metrics for reconciliation performance\n20: - Support leader election for high availability\n21: \n22: ## Architecture\n23: \n24: ### Package Structure\n25: \n26: ```\n27: pkg/workloadmanager/controller/\n28: ├── reconciler/\n29: │   ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntime reconciler implementation\n30: │   ├── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreter reconciler implementation\n31: │   ├── controller.go           # Controller setup and manager initialization\n32: │   ├── predicates.go           # Event filtering predicates\n33: │   ├── finalizers.go           # Finalizer management utilities\n34: │   ├── status.go               # Status condition management\n35: │   └── metrics.go              # Reconciler metrics\n36: ├── controller.go               # Existing HTTP-based controller (unchanged)\n37: └── sandbox.go                  # Existing sandbox creation logic (refactored)\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Component Interactions\n41: \n42: ```\n43: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                    Controller-Runtime Manager                   │\n45: │                                                                  │\n46: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n47: │  │              AgentRuntime Reconciler                     │   │\n48: │  │  - Watches AgentRuntime CRDs                             │   │\n49: │  │  - Reconciles on spec changes                            │   │\n50: │  │  - Manages Sandbox CR lifecycle                          │   │\n51: │  │  - Updates AgentRuntime.Status                           │   │\n52: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n53: │                                                                  │\n54: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n55: │  │            CodeInterpreter Reconciler                     │   │\n56: │  │  - Watches CodeInterpreter CRDs                          │   │\n57: │  │  - Reconciles on spec changes                            │   │\n58: │  │  - Manages Sandbox CR lifecycle                          │   │\n59: │  │  - Updates CodeInterpreter.Status                        │   │\n60: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n61: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62:           │                     │                     │\n63:           │                     │                     │\n64:           ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n65: ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n66: │  Kubernetes API  │  │   agent-sandbox  │  │     Redis        │\n67: │  (client-go)     │  │      API         │  │  (session store) │\n68: │  - AgentRuntime  │  │  - Sandbox CR    │  │  - Metadata      │\n69: │  - CodeInterpreter│ │  - SandboxClaim  │  │  - Activity TTL  │\n70: │  - Status updates│  │                  │  │                  │\n71: └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Reconciliation Flow\n75: \n76: ```\n77: Event Triggered (Create/Update/Delete)\n78:     ↓\n79: [Predicate Filter] Ignore if status-only update or deletion timestamp set\n80:     ↓\n81: [Reconcile Entrypoint] Load resource from cache\n82:     ↓\n83: [Finalizer Check] Add finalizer if not present (for cleanup)\n84:     ↓\n85: [Deletion Check] If deletion timestamp set:\n86:     - Delete associated sandbox resources\n87:     - Remove finalizer\n88:     - Return\n89:     ↓\n90: [Spec Validation] Validate spec fields\n91:     ↓\n92: [Desired State Calculation] Determine what needs to be created/updated\n93:     ↓\n94: [Sandbox Reconciliation] Create/update/delete Sandbox CR\n95:     ↓\n96: [Status Update] Update status conditions\n97:     ↓\n98: [Event Recording] Record Kubernetes events\n99:     ↓\n100: [Metrics Update] Update Prometheus metrics\n101:     ↓\n102: [Return] Result: Requeue or Done\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Data Structures\n106: \n107: ### Reconciler Structs\n108: \n109: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/agentruntime.go`\n110: \n111: ```go\n112: // AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n113: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n114: \tclient.Client\n115: \tScheme     *runtime.Scheme\n116: \tRecorder   record.EventRecorder\n117: \tSandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n118: \tStore       store.Store\n119: \tConfig      *controller.Config\n120: \n121: \t// Reconciliation configuration\n122: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n123: \tMaxReconciles int\n124: }\n125: \n126: // AgentRuntimeReconcilerOptions provides options for configuring the reconciler\n127: type AgentRuntimeReconcilerOptions struct {\n128: \tRateLimiter workqueue.RateLimiter\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go`\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: // CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\n136: type CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n137: \tclient.Client\n138: \tScheme       *runtime.Scheme\n139: \tRecorder     record.EventRecorder\n140: \tSandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n141: \tStore        store.Store\n142: \tConfig       *controller.Config\n143: \n144: \t// Reconciliation configuration\n145: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n146: \tMaxReconciles int\n147: }\n148: ```\n149: \n150: ### Status Conditions\n151: \n152: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n153: \n154: ```go\n155: // Condition types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n156: const (\n157: \t// ConditionTypeReady indicates the resource is ready to serve requests\n158: \tConditionTypeReady = \"Ready\"\n159: \t\n160: \t// ConditionTypeAvailable indicates the runtime is available\n161: \tConditionTypeAvailable = \"Available\"\n162: \t\n163: \t// ConditionTypeProgressing indicates the resource is being reconciled\n164: \tConditionTypeProgressing = \"Progressing\"\n165: \t\n166: \t// ConditionTypeError indicates an error occurred during reconciliation\n167: \tConditionTypeError = \"Error\"\n168: \t\n169: \t// ConditionTypeSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox resource was created\n170: \tConditionTypeSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n171: )\n172: \n173: // Reason constants\n174: const (\n175: \t// Reconciliation reasons\n176: \tReasonReconciliationStarted = \"ReconciliationStarted\"\n177: \tReasonReconciliationComplete = \"ReconciliationComplete\"\n178: \tReasonReconciliationFailed = \"ReconciliationFailed\"\n179: \t\n180: \t// Sandbox creation reasons\n181: \tReasonSandboxCreating = \"SandboxCreating\"\n182: \tReasonSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n183: \tReasonSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n184: \tReasonSandboxUpdating = \"SandboxUpdating\"\n185: \tReasonSandboxUpdated = \"SandboxUpdated\"\n186: \tReasonSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n187: \tReasonSandboxDeleting = \"SandboxDeleting\"\n188: \tReasonSandboxDeleted = \"SandboxDeleted\"\n189: \tReasonSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n190: \t\n191: \t// Validation reasons\n192: \tReasonValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n193: \tReasonSpecInvalid = \"SpecInvalid\"\n194: \t\n195: \t// Cleanup reasons\n196: \tReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n197: )\n198: \n199: // SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\n200: func SetCondition(status *metav1.ConditionManager, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time)\n201: \n202: // GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\n203: func GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition\n204: \n205: // IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\n206: func IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### Finalizers\n210: \n211: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers.go`\n212: \n213: ```go\n214: const (\n215: \t// FinalizerAgentRuntime is the finalizer for AgentRuntime resources\n216: \tFinalizerAgentRuntime = \"agentruntime.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n217: \t\n218: \t// FinalizerCodeInterpreter is the finalizer for CodeInterpreter resources\n219: \tFinalizerCodeInterpreter = \"codeinterpreter.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n220: )\n221: \n222: // AddFinalizer adds a finalizer to the resource if not already present\n223: func AddFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error\n224: \n225: // RemoveFinalizer removes a finalizer from the resource\n226: func RemoveFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error\n227: \n228: // HasFinalizer checks if the resource has the specified finalizer\n229: func HasFinalizer(obj client.Object, finalizer string) bool\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ### Predicates\n233: \n234: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/predicates.go`\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: // ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate filters events based on generation changes\n238: type ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate struct {\n239: \tpredicate.Funcs\n240: }\n241: \n242: // SetupWithManager registers the predicate with the controller\n243: func (p *ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n244: \n245: // LabelChangedPredicate filters events based on label changes\n246: type LabelChangedPredicate struct {\n247: \tpredicate.Funcs\n248: }\n249: \n250: // AnnotationChangedPredicate filters events based on annotation changes\n251: type AnnotationChangedPredicate struct {\n252: \tpredicate.Funcs\n253: }\n254: \n255: // PauseAnnotationPredicate filters events for resources with pause annotation\n256: type PauseAnnotationPredicate struct {\n257: \tpredicate.Funcs\n258: }\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Metrics\n262: \n263: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/metrics.go`\n264: \n265: ```go\n266: const (\n267: \t// Reconciler metrics\n268: \tmetricReconcileTotal = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_total\"\n269: \tmetricReconcileErrors = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_errors_total\"\n270: \tmetricReconcileDuration = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_duration_seconds\"\n271: \tmetricReconcileRequeues = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_requeues_total\"\n272: \t\n273: \t// Resource metrics\n274: \tmetricResourcesReady = \"workloadmanager_resources_ready\"\n275: \tmetricResourcesPending = \"workloadmanager_resources_pending\"\n276: \tmetricResourcesError = \"workloadmanager_resources_error\"\n277: \t\n278: \t// Sandbox metrics\n279: \tmetricSandboxCreations = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_creations_total\"\n280: \tmetricSandboxDeletions = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_deletions_total\"\n281: \tmetricSandboxUpdateDuration = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_update_duration_seconds\"\n282: )\n283: \n284: var (\n285: \treconcileTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n286: \t\tprometheus.CounterOpts{\n287: \t\t\tName: metricReconcileTotal,\n288: \t\t\tHelp: \"Total number of reconciliation operations\",\n289: \t\t},\n290: \t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n291: \t)\n292: \t\n293: \treconcileDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n294: \t\tprometheus.HistogramOpts{\n295: \t\t\tName:    metricReconcileDuration,\n296: \t\t\tHelp:    \"Reconciliation duration in seconds\",\n297: \t\t\tBuckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n298: \t\t},\n299: \t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"result\"},\n300: \t)\n301: \t\n302: \tresourcesReady = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n303: \t\tprometheus.GaugeOpts{\n304: \t\t\tName: metricResourcesReady,\n305: \t\t\tHelp: \"Number of ready resources\",\n306: \t\t},\n307: \t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"namespace\"},\n308: \t)\n309: )\n310: \n311: // RecordReconciliation records a reconciliation operation\n312: func RecordReconciliation(controller, namespace, name string, duration float64, result string)\n313: \n314: // RecordSandboxOperation records a sandbox operation\n315: func RecordSandboxOperation(operation, namespace, name string, duration float64, err error)\n316: ```\n317: \n318: ## API Contracts\n319: \n320: ### Reconciler Interfaces\n321: \n322: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go`\n323: \n324: ```go\n325: // Reconciler defines the interface for all reconcilers\n326: type Reconciler interface {\n327: \tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n328: \tSetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n329: }\n330: \n331: // ControllerConfig provides configuration for reconcilers\n332: type ControllerConfig struct {\n333: \t// RequeueAfter is the default requeue interval\n334: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n335: \t\n336: \t// MaxConcurrentReconciles is the maximum number of concurrent reconciles\n337: \tMaxConcurrentReconciles int\n338: \t\n339: \t// SyncPeriod is the full resync period\n340: \tSyncPeriod *time.Duration\n341: \t\n342: \t// EnableLeaderElection enables leader election\n343: \tEnableLeaderElection bool\n344: \t\n345: \t// LeaderElectionID is the leader election ID\n346: \tLeaderElectionID string\n347: \t\n348: \t// LeaderElectionNamespace is the namespace for leader election\n349: \tLeaderElectionNamespace string\n350: \t\n351: \t// MetricsAddr is the metrics server address\n352: \tMetricsAddr string\n353: \t\n354: \t// EnableProfiling enables profiling endpoints\n355: \tEnableProfiling bool\n356: \t\n357: \t// ProbeAddr is the health probe address\n358: \tProbeAddr string\n359: }\n360: \n361: // NewControllerManager creates a new controller manager\n362: func NewControllerManager(cfg *rest.Config, controllerCfg *ControllerConfig) (ctrl.Manager, error)\n363: \n364: // SetupWithManager sets up all controllers with the manager\n365: func SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, store store.Store, controllerCfg *ControllerConfig) error\n366: ```\n367: \n368: ### AgentRuntime Reconcile Method\n369: \n370: ```go\n371: // Reconcile reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n372: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n373: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n374: \tlog.Info(\"Reconciling AgentRuntime\", \"namespace\", req.Namespace, \"name\", req.Name)\n375: \t\n376: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n377: \t\n378: \t// Fetch the AgentRuntime instance\n379: \tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n380: \tif err := r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n381: \t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n382: \t\t\tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime resource not found. Ignoring since object must be deleted\")\n383: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n384: \t\t}\n385: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get AgentRuntime\")\n386: \t\tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n387: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n388: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n389: \t}\n390: \t\n391: \t// Check if resource is being deleted\n392: \tif !agentRuntime.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n393: \t\treturn r.reconcileDelete(ctx, agentRuntime)\n394: \t}\n395: \t\n396: \t// Add finalizer if not present\n397: \tif !HasFinalizer(agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime) {\n398: \t\tif err := AddFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime); err != nil {\n399: \t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to add finalizer\")\n400: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, err\n401: \t\t}\n402: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n403: \t}\n404: \t\n405: \t// Validate spec\n406: \tif err := r.validateSpec(agentRuntime); err != nil {\n407: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Spec validation failed\")\n408: \t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n409: \t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n410: \t\t\tReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n411: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n412: \t}\n413: \t\n414: \t// Reconcile sandbox\n415: \tsandboxResult, err := r.reconcileSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime)\n416: \tif err != nil {\n417: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to reconcile sandbox\")\n418: \t\tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n419: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n420: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n421: \t}\n422: \t\n423: \t// Update status based on sandbox result\n424: \tif sandboxResult.Created {\n425: \t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeSandboxCreated, \n426: \t\t\tReasonSandboxCreated, \"Sandbox resource created successfully\")\n427: \t}\n428: \t\n429: \t// Check if ready\n430: \tready := r.isReady(agentRuntime)\n431: \tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeReady, \n432: \t\tReasonReconciliationComplete, \"AgentRuntime is ready\")\n433: \t\n434: \t// Record metrics\n435: \tduration := time.Since(startTime).Seconds()\n436: \tresult := \"success\"\n437: \tif !ready {\n438: \t\tresult = \"requeue\"\n439: \t}\n440: \tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, duration, result)\n441: \t\n442: \t// Requeue if not ready\n443: \tif !ready {\n444: \t\tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime not ready, requeuing\")\n445: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n446: \t}\n447: \t\n448: \tlog.Info(\"Reconciliation completed successfully\")\n449: \treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n450: }\n451: ```\n452: \n453: ### CodeInterpreter Reconcile Method\n454: \n455: ```go\n456: // Reconcile reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\n457: func (r *CodeInterpreterReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n458: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n459: \tlog.Info(\"Reconciling CodeInterpreter\", \"namespace\", req.Namespace, \"name\", req.Name)\n460: \t\n461: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n462: \t\n463: \t// Fetch the CodeInterpreter instance\n464: \tcodeInterpreter := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}\n465: \tif err := r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, codeInterpreter); err != nil {\n466: \t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n467: \t\t\tlog.Info(\"CodeInterpreter resource not found. Ignoring since object must be deleted\")\n468: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n469: \t\t}\n470: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get CodeInterpreter\")\n471: \t\tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n472: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n473: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n474: \t}\n475: \t\n476: \t// Check if resource is being deleted\n477: \tif !codeInterpreter.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n478: \t\treturn r.reconcileDelete(ctx, codeInterpreter)\n479: \t}\n480: \t\n481: \t// Add finalizer if not present\n482: \tif !HasFinalizer(codeInterpreter, FinalizerCodeInterpreter) {\n483: \t\tif err := AddFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, codeInterpreter, FinalizerCodeInterpreter); err != nil {\n484: \t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to add finalizer\")\n485: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, err\n486: \t\t}\n487: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n488: \t}\n489: \t\n490: \t// Validate spec\n491: \tif err := r.validateSpec(codeInterpreter); err != nil {\n492: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Spec validation failed\")\n493: \t\tr.Recorder.Event(codeInterpreter, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n494: \t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n495: \t\t\tReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n496: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n497: \t}\n498: \t\n499: \t// Reconcile sandbox\n500: \tsandboxResult, err := r.reconcileSandbox(ctx, codeInterpreter)\n501: \tif err != nil {\n502: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to reconcile sandbox\")\n503: \t\tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n504: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n505: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n506: \t}\n507: \t\n508: \t// Update status based on sandbox result\n509: \tif sandboxResult.Created {\n510: \t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeSandboxCreated, \n511: \t\t\tReasonSandboxCreated, \"Sandbox resource created successfully\")\n512: \t}\n513: \t\n514: \t// Check if ready\n515: \tready := r.isReady(codeInterpreter)\n516: \tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeReady, \n517: \t\tReasonReconciliationComplete, \"CodeInterpreter is ready\")\n518: \t\n519: \t// Record metrics\n520: \tduration := time.Since(startTime).Seconds()\n521: \tresult := \"success\"\n522: \tif !ready {\n523: \t\tresult = \"requeue\"\n524: \t}\n525: \tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, duration, result)\n526: \t\n527: \t// Requeue if not ready\n528: \tif !ready {\n529: \t\tlog.Info(\"CodeInterpreter not ready, requeuing\")\n530: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n531: \t}\n532: \t\n533: \tlog.Info(\"Reconciliation completed successfully\")\n534: \treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n535: }\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ### Sandbox Reconciliation\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: // reconcileSandbox creates or updates the sandbox resource\n542: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcileSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n543: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n544: \t\n545: \tsandboxName := getSandboxName(agentRuntime)\n546: \t\n547: \t// Check if sandbox already exists\n548: \texistingSandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n549: \texistingSandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n550: \t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n551: \t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n552: \t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n553: \t})\n554: \t\n555: \terr := r.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n556: \t\tNamespace: agentRuntime.Namespace,\n557: \t\tName:      sandboxName,\n558: \t}, existingSandbox)\n559: \t\n560: \tif err != nil {\n561: \t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n562: \t\t\t// Create new sandbox\n563: \t\t\treturn r.createSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime, sandboxName)\n564: \t\t}\n565: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get sandbox: %w\", err)\n566: \t}\n567: \t\n568: \t// Update existing sandbox\n569: \treturn r.updateSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime, existingSandbox, sandboxName)\n570: }\n571: \n572: // createSandbox creates a new sandbox resource\n573: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) createSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sandboxName string) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n574: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n575: \tlog.Info(\"Creating sandbox\", \"name\", sandboxName)\n576: \t\n577: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n578: \t\n579: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n580: \tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n581: \t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n582: \t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n583: \t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n584: \t})\n585: \tsandbox.SetName(sandboxName)\n586: \tsandbox.SetNamespace(agentRuntime.Namespace)\n587: \t\n588: \t// Set labels\n589: \tlabels := map[string]string{\n590: \t\tconstants.LabelManagedBy:    constants.LabelManagedByValue,\n591: \t\tconstants.LabelWorkloadName: agentRuntime.Name,\n592: \t\tconstants.LabelKind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n593: \t}\n594: \tsandbox.SetLabels(labels)\n595: \t\n596: \t// Build spec from AgentRuntime spec\n597: \tspec, err := r.buildSandboxSpec(agentRuntime)\n598: \tif err != nil {\n599: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox spec: %w\", err)\n600: \t}\n601: \tsandbox.Object[\"spec\"] = spec\n602: \t\n603: \t// Create sandbox\n604: \tif err := r.Create(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n605: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to create sandbox\")\n606: \t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxCreateFailed, \n607: \t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to create sandbox: %v\", err))\n608: \t\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"create\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n609: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), err)\n610: \t\treturn nil, err\n611: \t}\n612: \t\n613: \tlog.Info(\"Sandbox created successfully\")\n614: \tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxCreated, \n615: \t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s created\", sandboxName))\n616: \tRecordSandboxOperation(\"create\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n617: \t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), nil)\n618: \t\n619: \treturn &SandboxResult{Created: true}, nil\n620: }\n621: \n622: // updateSandbox updates an existing sandbox resource\n623: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) updateSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, existing *unstructured.Unstructured, sandboxName string) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n624: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n625: \tlog.Info(\"Updating sandbox\", \"name\", sandboxName)\n626: \t\n627: \tstartTime := time.Now()\n628: \t\n629: \t// Build desired spec\n630: \tdesiredSpec, err := r.buildSandboxSpec(agentRuntime)\n631: \tif err != nil {\n632: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox spec: %w\", err)\n633: \t}\n634: \t\n635: \t// Check if update is needed\n636: \texistingSpec, _, _ := unstructured.NestedMap(existing.Object, \"spec\")\n637: \tif reflect.DeepEqual(desiredSpec, existingSpec) {\n638: \t\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox spec unchanged, skipping update\")\n639: \t\treturn &SandboxResult{Created: false}, nil\n640: \t}\n641: \t\n642: \t// Update sandbox\n643: \texisting.Object[\"spec\"] = desiredSpec\n644: \tif err := r.Update(ctx, existing); err != nil {\n645: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to update sandbox\")\n646: \t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxUpdateFailed, \n647: \t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to update sandbox: %v\", err))\n648: \t\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"update\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n649: \t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), err)\n650: \t\treturn nil, err\n651: \t}\n652: \t\n653: \tlog.Info(\"Sandbox updated successfully\")\n654: \tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxUpdated, \n655: \t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s updated\", sandboxName))\n656: \tRecordSandboxOperation(\"update\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n657: \t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), nil)\n658: \t\n659: \treturn &SandboxResult{Created: false}, nil\n660: }\n661: \n662: // SandboxResult represents the result of sandbox reconciliation\n663: type SandboxResult struct {\n664: \tCreated bool\n665: }\n666: ```\n667: \n668: ### Delete Reconciliation\n669: \n670: ```go\n671: // reconcileDelete handles deletion of AgentRuntime resources\n672: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcileDelete(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n673: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n674: \tlog.Info(\"Deleting AgentRuntime\", \"namespace\", agentRuntime.Namespace, \"name\", agentRuntime.Name)\n675: \t\n676: \t// Clean up sandbox resources\n677: \tsandboxName := getSandboxName(agentRuntime)\n678: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n679: \tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n680: \t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n681: \t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n682: \t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n683: \t})\n684: \t\n685: \terr := r.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n686: \t\tNamespace: agentRuntime.Namespace,\n687: \t\tName:      sandboxName,\n688: \t}, sandbox)\n689: \t\n690: \tif err == nil {\n691: \t\t// Delete sandbox\n692: \t\tif err := r.Delete(ctx, sandbox); err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n693: \t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to delete sandbox\")\n694: \t\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxDeleteFailed, \n695: \t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to delete sandbox: %v\", err))\n696: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n697: \t\t}\n698: \t\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox deleted successfully\")\n699: \t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxDeleted, \n700: \t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s deleted\", sandboxName))\n701: \t} else if !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n702: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get sandbox\")\n703: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n704: \t}\n705: \t\n706: \t// Remove finalizer\n707: \tif HasFinalizer(agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime) {\n708: \t\tif err := RemoveFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime); err != nil {\n709: \t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to remove finalizer\")\n710: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n711: \t\t}\n712: \t}\n713: \t\n714: \tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime deleted successfully\")\n715: \treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n716: }\n717: ```\n718: \n719: ## Error Handling\n720: \n721: ### Error Types\n722: \n723: ```go\n724: // ReconcilerError defines the reconciler error type\n725: type ReconcilerError struct {\n726: \tCode      string\n727: \tMessage   string\n728: \tErr       error\n729: \tRetryable bool\n730: }\n731: \n732: // Error implements the error interface\n733: func (e *ReconcilerError) Error() string {\n734: \tif e.Err != nil {\n735: \t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (caused by: %v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n736: \t}\n737: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n738: }\n739: \n740: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n741: func (e *ReconcilerError) Unwrap() error {\n742: \treturn e.Err\n743: }\n744: \n745: // Error codes\n746: const (\n747: \tErrCodeValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n748: \tErrCodeSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n749: \tErrCodeSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n750: \tErrCodeSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n751: \tErrCodeStatusUpdateFailed = \"StatusUpdateFailed\"\n752: \tErrCodeFinalizerFailed = \"FinalizerFailed\"\n753: \tErrCodeAPIServerError = \"APIServerError\"\n754: )\n755: \n756: // NewReconcilerError creates a new reconciler error\n757: func NewReconcilerError(code, message string, err error, retryable bool) *ReconcilerError {\n758: \treturn &ReconcilerError{\n759: \t\tCode:      code,\n760: \t\tMessage:   message,\n761: \t\tErr:       err,\n762: \t\tRetryable: retryable,\n763: \t}\n764: }\n765: ```\n766: \n767: ### Error Handling Strategy\n768: \n769: ```go\n770: // HandleReconcileError handles errors during reconciliation\n771: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) HandleReconcileError(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, err error) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n772: \tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n773: \t\n774: \tif apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n775: \t\tlog.Info(\"Conflict error, requeuing\")\n776: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, nil\n777: \t}\n778: \t\n779: \tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n780: \t\tlog.Info(\"Resource not found, ignoring\")\n781: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n782: \t}\n783: \t\n784: \tif reconcilerErr, ok := err.(*ReconcilerError); ok {\n785: \t\tif reconcilerErr.Retryable {\n786: \t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Retryable error, requeuing\")\n787: \t\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n788: \t\t\t\treconcilerErr.Code, reconcilerErr.Message)\n789: \t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n790: \t\t}\n791: \t\tlog.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error\")\n792: \t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n793: \t\t\treconcilerErr.Code, reconcilerErr.Message)\n794: \t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n795: \t}\n796: \t\n797: \t// Unknown error\n798: \tlog.Error(err, \"Unknown error during reconciliation\")\n799: \tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n800: \t\tErrCodeAPIServerError, err.Error())\n801: \treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n802: }\n803: ```\n804: \n805: ## Testing Strategy\n806: \n807: ### Unit Tests\n808: \n809: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/agentruntime_test.go`\n810: \n811: ```go\n812: package reconciler_test\n813: \n814: import (\n815: \t\"context\"\n816: \t\"testing\"\n817: \t\"time\"\n818: \n819: \t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n820: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n821: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n822: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n823: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n824: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake\"\n825: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n826: \n827: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n828: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\"\n829: )\n830: \n831: var _ = Describe(\"AgentRuntimeReconciler\", func() {\n832: \tvar (\n833: \t\tctx        context.Context\n834: \t\treconciler *reconciler.AgentRuntimeReconciler\n835: \t\tfakeClient client.Client\n836: \t\tscheme     *runtime.Scheme\n837: \t)\n838: \n839: \tBeforeEach(func() {\n840: \t\tctx = context.Background()\n841: \t\tscheme = runtime.NewScheme()\n842: \t\tExpect(runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)).To(Succeed())\n843: \t\t\n844: \t\tfakeClient = fake.NewClientBuilder().\n845: \t\t\tWithScheme(scheme).\n846: \t\t\tBuild()\n847: \t\t\n848: \t\treconciler = &reconciler.AgentRuntimeReconciler{\n849: \t\t\tClient:      fakeClient,\n850: \t\t\tScheme:      scheme,\n851: \t\t\tRequeueAfter: 10 * time.Second,\n852: \t\t}\n853: \t})\n854: \n855: \tContext(\"Reconcile creation\", func() {\n856: \t\tIt(\"should create sandbox resource for new AgentRuntime\", func() {\n857: \t\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n858: \t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n859: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n860: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n861: \t\t\t\t},\n862: \t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n863: \t\t\t\t\tPodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n864: \t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n865: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n866: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{\n867: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:  \"agent\",\n868: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n869: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n870: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n871: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n872: \t\t\t\t\t},\n873: \t\t\t\t},\n874: \t\t\t}\n875: \t\t\t\n876: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime)).To(Succeed())\n877: \t\t\t\n878: \t\t\treq := reconcile.Request{\n879: \t\t\t\tNamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n880: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n881: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n882: \t\t\t\t},\n883: \t\t\t}\n884: \t\t\t\n885: \t\t\tresult, err := reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, req)\n886: \t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n887: \t\t\tExpect(result.RequeueAfter).To(Equal(reconciler.RequeueAfter))\n888: \t\t\t\n889: \t\t\t// Verify sandbox was created\n890: \t\t\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n891: \t\t\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n892: \t\t\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n893: \t\t\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n894: \t\t\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n895: \t\t\t})\n896: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n897: \t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n898: \t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime-sandbox\",\n899: \t\t\t}, sandbox)).To(Succeed())\n900: \t\t})\n901: \n902: \t\tIt(\"should add finalizer to new AgentRuntime\", func() {\n903: \t\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n904: \t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n905: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n906: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n907: \t\t\t\t},\n908: \t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n909: \t\t\t\t\tPodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n910: \t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n911: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n912: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{\n913: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:  \"agent\",\n914: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n915: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n916: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n917: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n918: \t\t\t\t\t},\n919: \t\t\t\t},\n920: \t\t\t}\n921: \t\t\t\n922: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime)).To(Succeed())\n923: \t\t\t\n924: \t\t\treq := reconcile.Request{\n925: \t\t\t\tNamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n926: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n927: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n928: \t\t\t\t},\n929: \t\t\t}\n930: \t\t\t\n931: \t\t\t_, err := reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, req)\n932: \t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n933: \t\t\t\n934: \t\t\t// Verify finalizer was added\n935: \t\t\tupdated := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n936: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n937: \t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n938: \t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n939: \t\t\t}, updated)).To(Succeed())\n940: \t\t\tExpect(updated.Finalizers).To(ContainElement(reconciler.FinalizerAgentRuntime))\n941: \t\t})\n942: \t})\n943: \n944: \tContext(\"Reconcile deletion\", func() {\n945: \t\tIt(\"should delete sandbox resource when AgentRuntime is deleted\", func() {\n946: \t\t\t// Create AgentRuntime\n947: \t\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n948: \t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n949: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n950: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n951: \t\t\t\t\tFinalizers: []string{reconciler.FinalizerAgentRuntime},\n952: \t\t\t\t},\n953: \t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n954: \t\t\t\t\tPodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n955: \t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n956: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n957: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{\n958: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:  \"agent\",\n959: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n960: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n961: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n962: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n963: \t\t\t\t\t},\n964: \t\t\t\t},\n965: \t\t\t}\n966: \t\t\t\n967: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime)).To(Succeed())\n968: \t\t\t\n969: \t\t\t// Create sandbox\n970: \t\t\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n971: \t\t\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n972: \t\t\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n973: \t\t\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n974: \t\t\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n975: \t\t\t})\n976: \t\t\tsandbox.SetName(\"test-runtime-sandbox\")\n977: \t\t\tsandbox.SetNamespace(\"default\")\n978: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Create(ctx, sandbox)).To(Succeed())\n979: \t\t\t\n980: \t\t\t// Delete AgentRuntime\n981: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Delete(ctx, agentRuntime)).To(Succeed())\n982: \t\t\t\n983: \t\t\treq := reconcile.Request{\n984: \t\t\t\tNamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n985: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n986: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n987: \t\t\t\t},\n988: \t\t\t}\n989: \t\t\t\n990: \t\t\t_, err := reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, req)\n991: \t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n992: \t\t\t\n993: \t\t\t// Verify sandbox was deleted\n994: \t\t\terr = fakeClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n995: \t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n996: \t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime-sandbox\",\n997: \t\t\t}, sandbox)\n998: \t\t\tExpect(apierrors.IsNotFound(err)).To(BeTrue())\n999: \t\t})\n1000: \t})\n1001: \n1002: \tContext(\"Error handling\", func() {\n1003: \t\tIt(\"should handle invalid spec gracefully\", func() {\n1004: \t\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1005: \t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n1006: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n1007: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n1008: \t\t\t\t},\n1009: \t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n1010: \t\t\t\t\tPodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n1011: \t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n1012: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{},\n1013: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n1014: \t\t\t\t\t},\n1015: \t\t\t\t},\n1016: \t\t\t}\n1017: \t\t\t\n1018: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime)).To(Succeed())\n1019: \t\t\t\n1020: \t\t\treq := reconcile.Request{\n1021: \t\t\t\tNamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n1022: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n1023: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n1024: \t\t\t\t},\n1025: \t\t\t}\n1026: \t\t\t\n1027: \t\t\t_, err := reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, req)\n1028: \t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1029: \t\t\t\n1030: \t\t\t// Verify error condition was set\n1031: \t\t\tupdated := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n1032: \t\t\tExpect(fakeClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1033: \t\t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n1034: \t\t\t\tName:      \"test-runtime\",\n1035: \t\t\t}, updated)).To(Succeed())\n1036: \t\t\t\n1037: \t\t\terrorCondition := reconciler.GetCondition(updated.Status.Conditions, reconciler.ConditionTypeError)\n1038: \t\t\tExpect(errorCondition).NotTo(BeNil())\n1039: \t\t\tExpect(errorCondition.Status).To(Equal(metav1.ConditionFalse))\n1040: \t\t})\n1041: \t})\n1042: })\n1043: ```\n1044: \n1045: ### Integration Tests\n1046: \n1047: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/integration_test.go`\n1048: \n1049: ```go\n1050: package reconciler_test\n1051: \n1052: import (\n1053: \t\"context\"\n1054: \t\"testing\"\n1055: \t\"time\"\n1056: \n1057: \t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n1058: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n1059: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n1060: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/scheme\"\n1061: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n1062: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest\"\n1063: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager\"\n1064: \n1065: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n1066: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\"\n1067: )\n1068: \n1069: var (\n1070: \tenvTest   *envtest.Environment\n1071: \tk8sClient client.Client\n1072: \tmgr       manager.Manager\n1073: )\n1074: \n1075: var _ = BeforeSuite(func() {\n1076: \terr := runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme.Scheme)\n1077: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1078: \t\n1079: \tenvTest = &envtest.Environment{\n1080: \t\tCRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\n1081: \t\t\t\"../../../manifests/charts/base/crds\",\n1082: \t\t},\n1083: \t}\n1084: \t\n1085: \tcfg, err := envTest.Start()\n1086: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1087: \t\n1088: \tk8sClient, err = client.New(cfg, client.Options{Scheme: scheme.Scheme})\n1089: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1090: \t\n1091: \tmgr, err = manager.New(cfg, manager.Options{\n1092: \t\tScheme: scheme.Scheme,\n1093: \t})\n1094: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1095: \t\n1096: \tcontrollerCfg := &reconciler.ControllerConfig{\n1097: \t\tRequeueAfter:          10 * time.Second,\n1098: \t\tMaxConcurrentReconciles: 2,\n1099: \t}\n1100: \t\n1101: \terr = reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr, nil, controllerCfg)\n1102: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1103: \t\n1104: \tgo func() {\n1105: \t\terr = mgr.Start(context.Background())\n1106: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1107: \t}()\n1108: })\n1109: \n1110: var _ = AfterSuite(func() {\n1111: \terr := envTest.Stop()\n1112: \tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1113: })\n1114: \n1115: var _ = Describe(\"AgentRuntime Reconciler Integration\", func() {\n1116: \tContext(\"Full lifecycle\", func() {\n1117: \t\tIt(\"should create, update, and delete AgentRuntime with sandbox\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n1118: \t\t\tnamespace := \"default\"\n1119: \t\t\t\n1120: \t\t\t// Create AgentRuntime\n1121: \t\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n1122: \t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n1123: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime\",\n1124: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1125: \t\t\t\t},\n1126: \t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n1127: \t\t\t\t\tSessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n1128: \t\t\t\t\tMaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n1129: \t\t\t\t\tPodTemplate: &runtimev1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n1130: \t\t\t\t\t\tSpec: runtimev1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n1131: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tContainers: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n1132: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{\n1133: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:  \"agent\",\n1134: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tImage: \"python:3.11-slim\",\n1135: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tPorts: []runtimev1alpha1.SandboxContainerPort{\n1136: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{ContainerPort: 8080, Protocol: \"TCP\"},\n1137: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n1138: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n1139: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n1140: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n1141: \t\t\t\t\t},\n1142: \t\t\t\t},\n1143: \t\t\t}\n1144: \t\t\t\n1145: \t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime)\n1146: \t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n1147: \t\t\t\n1148: \t\t\t// Wait for sandbox to be created\n1149: \t\t\tEventually(func() bool {\n1150: \t\t\t\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n1151: \t\t\t\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n1152: \t\t\t\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n1153: \t\t\t\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n1154: \t\t\t\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n1155: \t\t\t\t})\n1156: \t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1157: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1158: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime-sandbox\",\n1159: \t\t\t\t}, sandbox)\n1160: \t\t\t\treturn err == nil\n1161: \t\t\t}, 30*time.Second, 2*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n1162: \t\t\t\n1163: \t\t\t// Verify AgentRuntime status\n1164: \t\t\tEventually(func() bool {\n1165: \t\t\t\tupdated := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n1166: \t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1167: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1168: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime\",\n1169: \t\t\t\t}, updated)\n1170: \t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n1171: \t\t\t\t\treturn false\n1172: \t\t\t\t}\n1173: \t\t\t\treturn reconciler.IsReady(updated.Status.Conditions)\n1174: \t\t\t}, 30*time.Second, 2*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n1175: \t\t\t\n1176: \t\t\t// Update AgentRuntime\n1177: \t\t\tEventually(func() error {\n1178: \t\t\t\tupdated := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n1179: \t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1180: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1181: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime\",\n1182: \t\t\t\t}, updated)\n1183: \t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n1184: \t\t\t\t\treturn err\n1185: \t\t\t\t}\n1186: \t\t\t\tupdated.Spec.SessionTimeout = &metav1.Duration{Duration: 30 * time.Minute}\n1187: \t\t\t\treturn k8sClient.Update(ctx, updated)\n1188: \t\t\t}, 10*time.Second, 2*time.Second).Should(Succeed())\n1189: \t\t\t\n1190: \t\t\t// Delete AgentRuntime\n1191: \t\t\tEventually(func() error {\n1192: \t\t\t\tupdated := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n1193: \t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1194: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1195: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime\",\n1196: \t\t\t\t}, updated)\n1197: \t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n1198: \t\t\t\t\treturn err\n1199: \t\t\t\t}\n1200: \t\t\t\treturn k8sClient.Delete(ctx, updated)\n1201: \t\t\t}, 10*time.Second, 2*time.Second).Should(Succeed())\n1202: \t\t\t\n1203: \t\t\t// Wait for sandbox to be deleted\n1204: \t\t\tEventually(func() bool {\n1205: \t\t\t\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n1206: \t\t\t\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n1207: \t\t\t\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n1208: \t\t\t\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n1209: \t\t\t\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n1210: \t\t\t\t})\n1211: \t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n1212: \t\t\t\t\tNamespace: namespace,\n1213: \t\t\t\t\tName:      \"integration-test-runtime-sandbox\",\n1214: \t\t\t\t}, sandbox)\n1215: \t\t\t\treturn apierrors.IsNotFound(err)\n1216: \t\t\t}, 30*time.Second, 2*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n1217: \t\t}, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n1218: \t})\n1219: })\n1220: ```\n1221: \n1222: ## Dependencies\n1223: \n1224: ### Go Module Dependencies\n1225: \n1226: ```go\n1227: require (\n1228:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.19.2\n1229:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log v0.19.2\n1230:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client v0.19.2\n1231:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile v0.19.2\n1232:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller v0.19.2\n1233:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/event v0.19.2\n1234:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/predicate v0.19.2\n1235:     sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager v0.19.2\n1236:     k8s.io/apimachinery v0.32.1\n1237:     k8s.io/api v0.32.1\n1238:     k8s.io/client-go v0.32.1\n1239:     sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox v0.6.0\n1240:     github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.20.5\n1241:     github.com/go-logr/logr v1.4.1\n1242:     k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n1243: )\n1244: ```\n1245: \n1246: ### Kubernetes RBAC Permissions\n1247: \n1248: ```yaml\n1249: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1250: kind: ClusterRole\n1251: metadata:\n1252:   name: agentcube-reconciler\n1253: rules:\n1254:   # AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n1255:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1256:     resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"agentruntimes/status\", \"agentruntimes/finalizers\"]\n1257:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n1258:   \n1259:   - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1260:     resources: [\"codeinterpreters\", \"codeinterpreters/status\", \"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]\n1261:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n1262:   \n1263:   # Sandbox resources\n1264:   - apiGroups: [\"agent-sandbox.volcano.sh\"]\n1265:     resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n1266:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"delete\"]\n1267:   \n1268:   # Events\n1269:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n1270:     resources: [\"events\"]\n1271:     verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n1272:   \n1273:   # ConfigMaps (for configuration)\n1274:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n1275:     resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n1276:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n1277: ```\n1278: \n1279: ## Integration Points\n1280: \n1281: ### With Existing Controller\n1282: \n1283: The new reconciler-based controllers will coexist with the existing HTTP-based controller:\n1284: \n1285: - The HTTP controller continues to handle on-demand sandbox creation for sessions\n1286: - The reconciler controllers handle the lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n1287: - Both use the same client-go and store interfaces\n1288: \n1289: ### With WorkloadManager\n1290: \n1291: The reconciler controllers are integrated into the WorkloadManager:\n1292: \n1293: - The controller manager is started as part of the WorkloadManager main process\n1294: - Shared configuration and dependencies are injected\n1295: - Metrics are exposed through the WorkloadManager metrics endpoint\n1296: \n1297: ### With Session Store\n1298: \n1299: The reconciler controllers may use the session store for:\n1300: \n1301: - Storing metadata about sandbox resources\n1302: - Tracking active sessions for a given AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n1303: - Implementing cleanup logic for orphaned sessions\n1304: \n1305: ## Documentation\n1306: \n1307: ### Configuration\n1308: \n1309: The reconciler configuration should be documented in `docs/configuration.md`:\n1310: \n1311: ```yaml\n1312: # Controller configuration\n1313: controller:\n1314:   # Requeue interval for reconciliation\n1315:   requeueAfter: 10s\n1316:   \n1317:   # Maximum number of concurrent reconciles per controller\n1318:   maxConcurrentReconciles: 2\n1319:   \n1320:   # Full resync period (optional)\n1321:   syncPeriod: 10m\n1322:   \n1323:   # Leader election\n1324:   enableLeaderElection: true\n1325:   leaderElectionID: \"agentcube-reconciler\"\n1326:   leaderElectionNamespace: \"agentcube-system\"\n1327:   \n1328:   # Metrics\n1329:   metricsAddr: \":8080\"\n1330:   enableProfiling: true\n1331:   \n1332:   # Health probes\n1333:   probeAddr: \":8081\"\n1334: ```\n1335: \n1336: ### Usage Examples\n1337: \n1338: **Example AgentRuntime with reconciler-managed sandbox** (`examples/agentruntime-reconciler.yaml`):\n1339: \n1340: ```yaml\n1341: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1342: kind: AgentRuntime\n1343: metadata:\n1344:   name: python-agent\n1345:   namespace: agentcube\n1346: spec:\n1347:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n1348:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n1349:   podTemplate:\n1350:     metadata:\n1351:       labels:\n1352:         app: python-agent\n1353:     spec:\n1354:       containers:\n1355:       - name: agent\n1356:         image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/python-agent:latest\n1357:         ports:\n1358:         - containerPort: 8080\n1359:           protocol: TCP\n1360:         resources:\n1361:           limits:\n1362:             cpu: \"500m\"\n1363:             memory: \"512Mi\"\n1364:           requests:\n1365:             cpu: \"100m\"\n1366:             memory: \"128Mi\"\n1367: ```\n1368: \n1369: The reconciler will automatically create and manage the sandbox resource for this AgentRuntime.\n1370: \n1371: ## Migration Path\n1372: \n1373: ### Phase 1: Implement Reconcilers\n1374: \n1375: - Implement AgentRuntimeReconciler and CodeInterpreterReconciler\n1376: - Add unit tests for both reconcilers\n1377: - Add integration tests using envtest\n1378: \n1379: ### Phase 2: Integrate with WorkloadManager\n1380: \n1381: - Add reconciler setup to WorkloadManager main process\n1382: - Enable controller manager with reconcilers\n1383: - Add configuration options for reconcilers\n1384: \n1385: ### Phase 3: Deploy and Validate\n1386: \n1387: - Deploy reconciler-based controllers\n1388: - Monitor metrics and logs\n1389: - Validate that sandbox resources are created and managed correctly\n1390: \n1391: ### Phase 4: Optional Migration\n1392: \n1393: - Evaluate whether to migrate HTTP-based sandbox creation to use reconciler\n1394: - Consider deprecating direct sandbox creation in favor of CRD-based approach\n1395: \n1396: ## Success Criteria\n1397: \n1398: - [ ] AgentRuntimeReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n1399: - [ ] CodeInterpreterReconciler successfully creates and manages sandbox resources\n1400: - [ ] Status conditions are accurately updated during reconciliation\n1401: - [ ] Finalizers are properly handled for resource deletion\n1402: - [ ] Events are recorded for all significant operations\n1403: - [ ] Metrics are exposed and can be scraped by Prometheus\n1404: - [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n1405: - [ ] Integration tests validate end-to-end reconciliation\n1406: - [ ] Error handling is robust and provides clear feedback\n1407: - [ ] Reconciler can handle spec changes gracefully\n1408: - [ ] Leader election works correctly in HA deployments\n\n(End of file - total 1408 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Design — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: L  \n**Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime, providing automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR implements a proper Kubernetes reconciler pattern using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. The reconcilers will watch for changes to these CRDs and automatically manage the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources, updating status conditions and ensuring the desired state is achieved.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Watch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs for create/update/delete events\n- Reconcile sandbox resources using the agent-sandbox API\n- Maintain accurate status conditions (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n- Handle spec changes gracefully (rolling updates, reconfiguration)\n- Implement proper event recording and finalizer handling\n- Provide metrics for reconciliation performance\n- Support leader election for high availability","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775847090137,"end":1775847090237}}}}
